          "credit": "US DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE",
          "content": "### SURVEILLANCE LOG: MISSION 3101\n**DATE:** October 14, 1962\n**SECTOR:** San Cristobal, Cuba\n\n**The U-2 Flight:**\nOn the morning of October 14, Major Richard Heyser piloted a U-2 spy plane at 70,000 feet over western Cuba. He was in Cuban airspace for only seven minutes, but in that brief window, his cameras snapped 928 high-resolution photographs. The film was rushed to the National Photographic Interpretation Center (NPIC) in Maryland, where analysts used light tables and calipers to examine every inch of the jungle terrain.\n\n**The Smoking Gun:**\nWhat they found has paralyzed the White House. The analysts identified a distinct 'trapezoidal pattern' of deployment—a layout that perfectly matches Soviet nuclear missile sites in Russia. The photos clearly show 'erector launchers,' fuel trailers, and oxidizer tanks. \n\n**The Threat:**\nThese are **SS-4 'Sandal' Medium-Range Ballistic Missiles (MRBMs)**. They are not defensive weapons; they are offensive First-Strike weapons. They carry a 1-megaton nuclear warhead—roughly 70 times more powerful than the bomb dropped on Hiroshima. Intelligence estimates we have a window of **10 to 13 days** before the sites are fully operational. Once they are active, the US Early Warning System is useless."
