          "content": "### THREAT RADIUS CALCULATION\n\nThis classified projection map displays the lethal reach of the verified SS-4 (1,000 nautical miles) and the suspected SS-5 (2,200 nautical miles) sites.\n\n**Strategic Decapitation:**\nThe presence of these missiles fundamentally breaks the Cold War doctrine of Mutually Assured Destruction (MAD). Typically, if the Soviets launched an ICBM from Russia, US radar would detect it 25 minutes before impact, giving the President time to order a counter-launch. \n\n**The Zero-Warning Reality:**\nA missile launched from San Cristobal would hit Washington D.C. in less than **15 minutes**. It would hit Dallas, St. Louis, or Cape Canaveral even faster. This 'short flight time' means the US Command Authority (the President and Pentagon) could be wiped out before they could pick up the red phone. \n\n**The Political Calculus:**\nKhrushchev is likely gambling. He knows the US has Jupiter missiles in Turkey aimed at him. By placing missiles in Cuba, he is trying to level the playing field—or perhaps he plans to use them as a bargaining chip to force the US out of West Berlin."
