          "credit": "USAF / GEN. LEMAY",
          "content": "### PROFILE: GENERAL CURTIS LEMAY\n**Chief of Staff, US Air Force**\n\nLeMay is the archetype of the Cold War warrior. He commanded the firebombing of Tokyo in WWII and believes in overwhelming force. He views the President's hesitation as weakness.\n\n**The Confrontation:**\nIn a heated exchange, LeMay cornered the President: *'This blockade and political action lead to war. This is almost as bad as the appeasement at Munich.'* Comparing Kennedy to Neville Chamberlain (who appeased Hitler) is a direct insult.\n\n**The Military Guarantee:**\nLeMay assures the room that the Air Force can destroy 90% of the missiles in the first sortie. When Kennedy asks about the remaining 10%, LeMay dismisses the risk. But the President knows that even one surviving missile could obliterate Miami. The Chiefs believe war is inevitable and that it is better to strike while the US still has the advantage."
