          "content": "### THE NAVY FLAG PLOT\n\n**TIME:** 10:00 AM EST\n\nThe Quarantine is active. An armada of US destroyers, cruisers, and the aircraft carrier *USS Essex* has formed a picket line 500 nautical miles from the Cuban coast. The order is clear: Any vessel crossing the line must stop and submit to inspection.\n\n**The Crisis Point:**\nIntelligence reports that two Soviet cargo ships, the *Gagarin* and the *Komiles*, are steaming directly toward the line. They are not slowing down. Between them and the US fleet lies a Soviet Foxtrot-class submarine.\n\n**Civilian Control:**\nThe President is personally managing the positioning of individual ships from the White House, bypassing the naval chain of command. This enrages Chief of Naval Operations George Anderson, who famously snaps at McNamara: *'The Navy has been running blockades since John Paul Jones. Go back to your office.'* But Kennedy knows that a single trigger-happy captain could spark a nuclear exchange."
