          "content": "### THE COURT OF PUBLIC OPINION\n\nThe crisis has shifted from the secret Situation Room to the public arena of the United Nations Security Council in New York. The world is watching on live television.\n\n**The Credibility Gap:**\nSoviet Ambassador Valerian Zorin has been stonewalling. He claims the accusations of missiles in Cuba are 'CIA fabrications' and 'American hysteria.' Many neutral nations—and even some US allies—are skeptical. They remember the Bay of Pigs and think the US is just looking for an excuse to invade Cuba.\n\n**The Gamble:**\nUS Ambassador Adlai Stevenson has requested permission to reveal the Top Secret U-2 photos. This is a massive security risk. It shows the Soviets exactly what our cameras can see (resolution, depth, analysis techniques). But ExComm decides that winning the information war is worth the intelligence cost. Stevenson enters the chamber armed with easels and blown-up photographs."
