          "credit": "SA-2 GUIDELINE SITE",
          "content": "### LOSING CONTROL\n\n**Field Analysis:**\nThe shootdown changes the entire calculation. It implies the Soviets have moved from a defensive posture to open combat. \n\n**The Command Breakdown:**\nHowever, intelligence analysis (confirmed years later) suggests a terrifying reality: Khrushchev did *not* order the shootdown. The order was given by a local Soviet commander, General Grechko or Pliyev, who was acting on his own initiative because he thought an invasion was imminent.\n\n**The Chaos Factor:**\nThis means Moscow is losing control of its own forces in Cuba. If the US strikes the SAM site in retaliation, as the Generals demand, the local Soviet commanders might panic and launch their tactical nuclear weapons (FROGs) or even the MRBMs at the US invasion fleet. We are no longer negotiating with a rational government; we are negotiating with the chaos of the battlefield."
