          "content": "### THE TURKEY PROBLEM\n\n**The Reality:**\nThe Jupiter missiles in Turkey are obsolete liquid-fueled relics. The US was already planning to scrap them in six months and replace them with invincible Polaris submarine-based missiles. \n\n**The Dilemma:**\nHowever, publicly trading them under Soviet threat would destroy NATO. It would look like the US was selling out an ally (Turkey) to save its own skin. \n\n**The 'Cordier' Ploy' (Secret Deal):**\nJFK sends RFK to meet Soviet Ambassador Anatoly Dobrynin secretly at the Department of Justice. RFK delivers a strict ultimatum: \n1.  We accept the non-invasion pledge.\n2.  We **cannot** make a public deal about Turkey.\n3.  **HOWEVER**, if the Soviets remove their missiles, the US will dismantle the Jupiters in Turkey within 4-5 months. \n4.  This is a 'private assurance,' not a treaty. If the Soviets ever speak of this deal publicly, the US will deny it."
