          "content": "### THE DEADLINE\n\n**TIME:** Sunday Morning, October 28\n\nThe secret offer has been delivered. RFK has left the Soviet Embassy. He told Dobrynin that if the Soviets do not commit to removing the missiles by tomorrow, the United States will commence military action.\n\n**The Silence:**\nThe White House is waiting. There is no guarantee Khrushchev will accept the deal. He might view the 'secret promise' as a trick. He might be unable to convince his own hardliners in the Kremlin to back down.\n\n**The Stakes:**\nGeneral LeMay has the bombers on the runway. The invasion fleet is in position. If Radio Moscow does not broadcast a message of withdrawal in the next few hours, Operation Scabbards (the invasion of Cuba) will begin. The fate of the world hangs on whether one man in Moscow decides to blink."
